&nbsp;After being shown at the Sundance Film Festival earlier this year, magical movie &#8220;Sleight&#8221; now has a first teaser trailer, reports SlashFilm.The film tells the story of Bo, a gifted high school student and street magician who, after the death of his mother, has to take charge of his little sister Tina.But the money Bo earns through his magical street acts is not enough, leading him into a world of drugs, clubs and parties as he begins working for local drug dealer Angelo where he must use his magical skills to survive.The movie stars &#8220;The Maze Runner&#8221;&#8216;s Jacob Latimore as Bo alongside &#8220;12 Years a Slave&#8221; actress Storm Redi as Tina, with &#8220;The West Wing&#8221;&#8216;s Dul Hill as Angelo.&#8220;Sleight&#8221; will be released in theaters on April 7, 2017.-Relaxnews